  <p>
      <b>Background:</b>
  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/messages/clinical_content/overviews/national_joint_registry_data_set_overviews/national_joint_registry_data_set_introduction.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National Joint Registry Data Set</xref>
 collects information on primary 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_joint_replacement_surgery">Joint Replacement Surgery</xref>
 and revision 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_joint_replacement_surgery">Joint Replacement Surgery</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The majority of 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/messages/clinical_content/overviews/national_joint_registry_data_set_overviews/national_joint_registry_data_set_introduction.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National Joint Registry Data Set</xref>
 items relate to the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
's operation details and are collected in the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_operating_theatre">OPERATING THEATRE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The National Codes for National Joint Registry items match the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">National Joint Registry</xref>
 bulk upload codes / system generated codes.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 must give their consent for this data to be recorded on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_national_joint_registry">National Joint Registry</xref>
 Data Entry System (the electronic system for collection and transfer of data).   </p>
  <p>
      <i>Note: the consent is for data in the 'Patient Identifiers' group. Where consent is not given, the 'Patient Details' group and the operation details are still recorded.</i>
  </p>
